so I thought...

12:27.047 --> 12:28.947
It's called a pause.

12:28.949 --> 12:30.415
Right.

12:32.419 --> 12:34.919
Sorry. It doesn't say
pause on my script...

12:34.921 --> 12:36.788
Well, it doesn't say suck,
either, yet here we are.

12:40.193 --> 12:41.960
You know your size?

12:41.962 --> 12:43.595
Always tended toward the slim.

12:43.597 --> 12:45.063
I don't see that changing much

12:45.065 --> 12:47.499
at this point.

12:49.870 --> 12:51.603
Try these.

12:51.605 --> 12:53.738
Afterwards, we'll swing
by the pharmacy,

12:53.740 --> 12:56.541
get those medications that
the doctor wrote for you.

12:56.543 --> 12:58.409
Sounds like a plan.

12:58.411 --> 13:00.712
Ugh! $100?

13:00.714 --> 13:02.781
It's what they cost.

13:02.783 --> 13:06.050
I'm paying, just take the pants.

13:12.993 --> 13:15.460
So are we gonna talk
about it or not?

13:15.462 --> 13:16.795
Talk about what?

13:16.797 --> 13:19.764
Ha. About what.
Uh, this morning.

13:19.766 --> 13:23.234
Or are you content to stand in
silent judgment with that face?

13:23.236 --> 13:24.769
It's just my face.

13:24.771 --> 13:27.405
No, you didn't like me
apologizing for you.

13:27.407 --> 13:28.907
I get it.

13:28.909 --> 13:31.176
Would you have been happier
if I made a big scene?

13:31.178 --> 13:32.744
You know, got up in Tony's face,

13:32.746 --> 13:35.013
had the cops roll up
and turn the hoses on us?

13:35.015 --> 13:37.415
It's the cosgroves.

13:37.417 --> 13:40.351
He runs an insurance agency,
she collects owls.

13:40.353 --> 13:43.154
History would not have
memorialized our stand.

13:43.156 --> 13:44.489
You ever had a hose
turned on you?

13:44.491 --> 13:45.990
Can't say that I have,
I'm very sorry.

13:45.992 --> 13:48.159
Don't be. It hurts.

13:48.161 --> 13:49.828
And there's that face.

13:49.830 --> 13:51.863
Only face I got.
Look, I could use some socks...

13:51.865 --> 13:54.132
No, the face. The one
that says I have a scar

13:54.134 --> 13:56.201
on my arm from
integrating schools.

13:56.203 --> 13:58.970
And probably blisters on your
feet from marching for freedom,

13:58.972 --> 14:01.506
but me, because I grew up
in a white house,

14:01.508 --> 14:04.042
you think I don't live
in a black man's world.

14:04.044 --> 14:05.643
Oh, you know the one.

14:05.645 --> 14:08.112
The one where that salesman
there has been eyeballing us

14:08.114 --> 14:10.381
ever since we came in here.
Or where that security guard

14:10.383 --> 14:11.449
has moved just a little

14:11.451 --> 14:13.051
off his mark so he can
keep us in his sight.

14:13.053 --> 14:14.652
And where they'll definitely ask

14:14.654 --> 14:16.855
for an ID with my credit card
when I go to pay,

14:16.857 --> 14:19.224
even though they haven't
asked for anybody else's.

14:19.226 --> 14:21.059
Plus a million
things every day

14:21.061 --> 14:24.128
that I have to <i> choose</i> to let go,

14:24.130 --> 14:27.866
just so I'm not
pissed off all the time.

14:27.868 --> 14:29.968
Like I did on the street
this morning.

14:29.970 --> 14:33.071
Like I have done
every day of my life.

14:35.475 --> 14:38.176
Now try on the damn
slim cut flat front chinos.

14:38.178 --> 14:41.479
I think they'll
look nice on you.

14:49.923 --> 14:51.656
Randall!
Yeah?

14:51.658 --> 14:53.157
Watch!

14:53.159 --> 14:55.894
Cool! Cool!

14:55.896 --> 14:58.529
Dad, watch! Dad!

14:58.531 --> 15:00.064
Where's the other one?
I'm looking.

15:00.066 --> 15:01.833
Man, you take your
eyes off one for

15:01.835 --> 15:03.534
a second, you lose track
of the others.

15:03.536 --> 15:04.836
That's because
there are more of them

15:04.838 --> 15:06.070
than there are of us.

15:06.072 --> 15:07.105
Always will be.

15:07.107 --> 15:08.406
What? Oh.

15:08.408 --> 15:09.774
Talking about the kids.

15:09.776 --> 15:12.243
Yep. It's a war.
They got the numbers.

15:12.245 --> 15:14.178
Dad! Dad!
We were beat before we started.

15:14.180 --> 15:15.780
Watch!
There she is.
Oh.

15:15.782 --> 15:17.015
Hi. Hey, guys.

15:17.017 --> 15:18.349
You want to play mermaids?

15:18.351 --> 15:20.151
This is from all of us.

15:23.924 --> 15:25.189
Dad!

15:25.191 --> 15:27.625
Dad! Daddy! Dad!
Yep.

15:27.627 --> 15:29.127
Dad, watch me!

15:29.129 --> 15:30.395
Yeah. I see you, pal!

15:30.397 --> 15:31.896
Do you remember
the first time

15:31.898 --> 15:33.965
he said "dad"?
How happy I was?

15:33.967 --> 15:35.433
Now where's Randall?

15:35.435 --> 15:38.102
How about that time?
Did you see?

15:38.104 --> 15:39.470
Hey, kev. Where's your brother?

15:39.472 --> 15:40.805
I don't know!

15:40.807 --> 15:41.906
Jack...

15:41.908 --> 15:43.207
You take land, I'll take sea.

15:43.209 --> 15:45.910
Dad! Watch!

15:45.912 --> 15:47.445
Kevin.

15:47.447 --> 15:49.213
You were supposed
to watch each other!

15:49.215 --> 15:51.416
Randall!

15:51.418 --> 15:54.352
Randall!

15:57.424 --> 15:59.757
<i> Aw, Kate it was</i>
<i> the worst audition</i>

15:59.759 --> 16:01.993
in the history of the world.
Okay? I mean, that woman

16:01.995 --> 16:03.828
made me so nervous, I started
doing an English accent

16:03.830 --> 16:05.630
in the middle of it
for no reason!

16:05.632 --> 16:07.665
Okay, I'm sure it
wasn't <i> that bad.</i>

16:07.667 --> 16:09.267
Maybe that's the problem.
You know?

16:09.269 --> 16:10.935
I wanted it too much.
Hey! It's the man-NY!

16:10.937 --> 16:12.503
Hey man-NY! How's it going?

16:12.505 --> 16:14.172
Yeah. Listen. Could you
please fly out here?

16:14.174 --> 16:15.673
I really need you right now.

16:15.675 --> 16:18.109
You'll be fine, you just...

16:18.111 --> 16:20.244
What? I'm just what?
Where'd you go?

16:20.246 --> 16:21.846
Nowhere. I'm here.
I'm shopping.

16:21.848 --> 16:23.514
I'm lost.
- You're not lost.

16:23.516 --> 16:25.283
It's just all new.
It's just new.

16:25.285 --> 16:28.152
No... I mean I'm actually lost,

16:28.154 --> 16:30.455
I have no idea where the hell
I'm at. I got to go.

16:30.457 --> 16:31.756
Oh!
Ow!

16:31.758 --> 16:33.825
Sorry. Oh.

16:34.761 --> 16:36.661
Hey, uh...

16:36.663 --> 16:38.763
That whole thing back
there, just so you know.

16:38.765 --> 16:40.631
I'm not actually bad, okay?

16:40.633 --> 16:42.033
Okay. Duly noted.
Okay.

16:42.035 --> 16:43.301
Okay. Just wanted
to get that out there.

16:43.303 --> 16:44.936
Well, out there it is.

16:44.938 --> 16:47.005
Although you weren't
super helpful.

16:50.610 --> 16:52.510
You want to get a drink?

16:52.512 --> 16:54.112
What, like, now?

16:54.114 --> 16:56.614
Yeah. Now.
Come on,

16:56.616 --> 16:58.549
L.A.
what? Yeah.

17:03.656 --> 17:06.891
<i>Mom, the play's about to start!</i>

17:06.893 --> 17:09.359
All right, Tess. Hurry up.
Go get your dress on.
Get her her shoes.

17:09.362 --> 17:10.528
Hurry, hurry, hurry.
Break a leg.

17:10.530 --> 17:12.864
Come on...

17:12.866 --> 17:15.366
Wow, this is a nice place.

17:15.367 --> 17:17.635
Yeah. Public schools
in this area are good,

17:17.637 --> 17:18.736
it's why we moved here.

17:18.738 --> 17:20.338
Even better than private.

17:20.339 --> 17:22.507
Mm-hmm.
You know, the parents
are real involved.

17:22.509 --> 17:24.709
Mm-hmm.
You know, Beth's on the board.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.978
Real involved.

17:28.147 --> 17:29.414
They got a farm.

17:29.416 --> 17:31.582
Really?
Yeah. Out back.

17:31.584 --> 17:34.552
Kids learn about the land.
Grow their own food.

17:34.554 --> 17:37.088
Thank you.

17:37.090 --> 17:39.424
They got, uh, chickens.

17:39.426 --> 17:41.392
They got a goat.

17:42.862 --> 17:47.098
* Wanna take it down,
gonna do my thing *

17:47.100 --> 17:49.867
* gonna do my thing *

17:49.869 --> 17:52.703
* gonna do
my thing *

17:52.705 --> 17:54.072
* gonna do my thing *

17:54.074 --> 17:55.940
hi.

17:55.942 --> 17:58.176
Can I help you find something?

17:58.178 --> 17:59.243
No.

17:59.245 --> 18:01.245
Oh! You're here about the job.

18:02.215 --> 18:03.381
Hmm?

18:03.383 --> 18:04.549
You know. The job?

18:04.551 --> 18:06.050
Y-yeah.

18:06.052 --> 18:07.351
Great!

18:07.353 --> 18:08.786
* I'm unstoppable *

18:08.788 --> 18:11.456
let's go over here
so we can talk.

18:11.458 --> 18:14.158
* It's time to hit
the road again. *

18:21.634 --> 18:24.435
Randall?
Ugh... Randall.

18:24.437 --> 18:25.470
Hey,

18:25.472 --> 18:27.572
Kate. Have you seen Randall?

18:27.574 --> 18:29.474
Randall!

18:45.291 --> 18:47.325
Randall?

18:47.327 --> 18:48.960
Randall...

18:50.630 --> 18:52.964
Randall! Hello!

18:52.966 --> 18:54.432
Did you not hear me calling you?

18:54.434 --> 18:56.434
Hey, what are you
doing over here?
Oh, no, no, no...

18:56.436 --> 18:58.636
I've been...
It's okay.
I'm watching him.

18:58.638 --> 19:00.404
Okay, it's... i-i have
him now. I'm sorry,

19:00.406 --> 19:02.507
I'm his mother. I was a
little panicked. I'm Rebecca.

19:02.509 --> 19:03.774
Oh, we know who you are.

19:03.776 --> 19:05.076
You do?

19:05.078 --> 19:07.311
Oh yes. When a white
family has a black child

19:07.313 --> 19:09.580
and they don't introduce
themselves to any of us,

19:09.582 --> 19:11.582
we tend to take notice.

19:12.986 --> 19:15.586
Well. Thank you
for watching him,

19:15.588 --> 19:17.855
he's just not
supposed to be over here.

19:19.359 --> 19:21.826
Not... "Over here" like that.

19:21.828 --> 19:25.096
There's nothing wrong
with over here.

19:25.098 --> 19:29.167
I just mean that I want him
where we can see him.

19:29.169 --> 19:30.868
Where we're sitting.
In front of us.

19:30.870 --> 19:32.837
Thank you. It was very nice
to meet you.

19:32.839 --> 19:34.172
Randall, come on. Let's go.

19:34.174 --> 19:36.374
Come on. Thank you.

19:38.678 --> 19:39.944
Actually,

19:39.946 --> 19:41.979
you stay right here.

19:41.981 --> 19:45.116
That's my son,
and I'm his mother.

19:45.118 --> 19:47.518
And I don't know if you have
some sort of problem
with that arrangement,

19:47.520 --> 19:49.053
but also, I don't really care.

19:49.055 --> 19:51.022
Thank you very much
for watching my son.

19:51.024 --> 19:52.290
But I have him now.

19:52.292 --> 19:54.025
Okay.
Okay.

19:54.027 --> 19:56.394
You need to get the child
a proper haircut.

19:57.530 --> 19:59.830
The razor bumps on his neck.

19:59.832 --> 20:02.633
You need a barber who knows
how to cut black hair.

20:04.537 --> 20:06.237
Come on.

20:06.239 --> 20:08.639
Hey, I told you to stay with
your brother. Didn't I?

20:08.641 --> 20:10.374
Sorry.

20:10.376 --> 20:12.843
Is this the real reason you
wanted to come to this pool

20:12.845 --> 20:14.545
and not the other?

20:14.547 --> 20:16.814
Come on.

20:33.499 --> 20:35.866
So beautiful.

20:35.868 --> 20:38.269
Ho, there. Who might you be,

20:38.271 --> 20:39.337
fair maid?

20:39.339 --> 20:41.205
I am the princess snow white.

20:43.409 --> 20:45.543
I have traveled this land

20:45.545 --> 20:48.379
and many others,
and never have I seen

20:48.381 --> 20:50.681
a beauty so fair.

20:51.784 --> 20:53.251
Where are you from,

20:53.253 --> 20:54.418
noble sir?

20:54.420 --> 20:55.753
What errand brings you

20:55.755 --> 20:57.054
to the forest?

20:59.292 --> 21:01.292
I come from a land far away.

21:13.740 --> 21:14.772
thanks.
Cheers.

21:18.378 --> 21:20.077
The, uh...
Thank you.

21:20.079 --> 21:21.145
...that play is really special,
isn't it?

21:21.147 --> 21:22.947
I mean, I don't read
a lot of plays,

21:22.949 --> 21:24.915
but that's-that's good.
- Yeah. Yeah, I got that.

21:24.917 --> 21:26.584
No, look, it's...

21:26.586 --> 21:27.818
It's really good,

21:27.820 --> 21:29.553
actually.
I mean, it's...

21:29.555 --> 21:30.788
It's fragile.

21:30.790 --> 21:32.356
It's-it's delicate.

21:35.428 --> 21:37.395
So, where are you from,
Kevin Pearson?

21:37.397 --> 21:38.629
Me?
Mm.

21:38.631 --> 21:40.298
Uh... Pittsburgh, originally.

21:40.300 --> 21:42.066
You got family back there?

21:42.068 --> 21:44.969
Um... not anymore.

21:44.971 --> 21:46.971
Right, so, L.A. is home now?

21:48.508 --> 21:49.840
Yeah, I guess so.

21:49.842 --> 21:52.076
Yeah.

21:52.078 --> 21:53.911
I think you should
go back there.

21:53.913 --> 21:55.680
I know, right?

21:58.117 --> 21:59.250
Are you serious?

21:59.252 --> 22:01.619
I am serious.

22:01.621 --> 22:04.121
And I'm telling you
this as a friend

22:04.123 --> 22:06.257
because I see
this all the time.

22:06.259 --> 22:08.426
I mean, you said it yourself.

22:08.428 --> 22:11.028
Pretty people come here
from TV or movies

22:11.030 --> 22:12.763
because they want to do
something real.

22:12.765 --> 22:13.964
I mean, even if they've...

22:13.966 --> 22:16.000
They've never had
a genuine moment

22:16.002 --> 22:18.302
in their entire lives.

22:18.304 --> 22:20.271
Do you know what they find out?

22:20.273 --> 22:21.806
That guess what?

22:21.808 --> 22:23.541
It's hard.

22:23.543 --> 22:24.975
It's so hard.

22:24.977 --> 22:25.976
It's not...

22:25.978 --> 22:27.111
It's not pretend,

22:27.113 --> 22:28.713
it's not <i> guys and dolls</i>

22:28.715 --> 22:30.114
in some high school
cafeteria.

22:30.116 --> 22:31.949
It's not...

22:31.951 --> 22:33.851
I'm sorry, what-what-what
was the-the movie you were in?

22:34.821 --> 22:36.387
It was a TV show, actually,

22:36.389 --> 22:37.688
called, uh,<i> the man-NY.</i>

22:37.690 --> 22:38.956
Yeah, and look,

22:38.958 --> 22:39.957
I'm not saying that

22:39.959 --> 22:40.958
you're not good at what you do.

22:40.960 --> 22:41.959
I'm sure you're...

22:41.961 --> 22:43.027
You're great at it.

22:43.029 --> 22:44.562
I mean, i-i couldn't do it.

22:44.564 --> 22:47.398
But this...
Is not that.

22:48.368 --> 22:49.567
You're in over your head,

22:49.569 --> 22:50.668
Kevin Pearson.

22:50.670 --> 22:52.136
I mean, if you really want

22:52.138 --> 22:53.838
to do this, then go home,

22:53.840 --> 22:56.240
find a class,
get some training.

22:57.877 --> 22:59.009
I'm just being honest.

22:59.011 --> 23:01.345
I see.

23:01.347 --> 23:02.480
As a... as a friend.

23:02.482 --> 23:03.514
Yeah.
Yeah.

23:04.851 --> 23:05.983
Still, just, you know,
it feels like

23:05.985 --> 23:07.051
you're using the word
"friend" wrong.

23:11.391 --> 23:12.390
Everything all right?

23:12.392 --> 23:14.158
You okay?
Yeah.

23:14.160 --> 23:15.192
Yeah?

23:15.194 --> 23:17.361
Yeah.

23:17.363 --> 23:19.497
You got the part.

23:19.499 --> 23:20.765
Wait, I'm sorry, what?
They think the nanny

23:20.767 --> 23:22.600
will sell tickets.

23:27.607 --> 23:29.707
It was actually <i> the man-NY.</i>

23:29.709 --> 23:31.175
Dad, look!

23:31.177 --> 23:32.676
I'm going under and everything!

23:32.678 --> 23:33.711
Dad!

23:33.713 --> 23:35.913
Yeah, I see you, pal!
Randall.

23:35.915 --> 23:37.381
Dad!
Lunch, baby.

23:37.383 --> 23:38.716
Dad!
You know,
maybe she was just

23:38.718 --> 23:40.017
trying to be helpful.
- Dad! Watch!

23:40.019 --> 23:41.285
By condescendingly

23:41.287 --> 23:43.087
telling me how I could
raise my kid? Yeah.

23:43.089 --> 23:44.388
No, thank you.

23:44.390 --> 23:45.623
Dad!

23:55.468 --> 23:57.568
* I love my father
and I love him well... *

